And that's where data comes into play:Â data teaches us how and where to take initiative in order to create the most impactful results, both economically and sustainably. "Before SustainIQ, we were working hard on our sustainability goals, but had no way to bring all that information together for tenders, Board reports or customer presentations and we couldn’t evidence our impact. Now, SustainIQ gives us all that rich data at the touch of a button and it’s been transformational. We’ve won new business with more ease and been able to demonstrate our impact to make staff and customers proud to be engaged with us." SustainIQ helps with delivery of Section 106 commitmentsSustainIQ was formed by its two co-founders Liam McEvoy and Maria Diffley. The pair met at an industry award ceremony in 2017 and over a glass or two of wine, got chatting about the many challenges sustainability presents to businesses who are looking to operate in a more sustainable and responsible manner. Many more conversations followed, and they soon realised there was a real need to create a solution that would help organisations use their sustainability performance to drive business improvement. And so, SustainIQ was born. An online platform that allows organisations to harness their business intelligence that previously was not being considered in the strategic decision-making process.

Both Maria and Liam have strong backgrounds working in sustainability. Maria has worked in both the public and voluntary sectors and holds an MSc in Sustainability & CSR.
